<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-04T10:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-04T10:24:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">760c.60m/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-04T17:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">June 4,
                                            1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:12
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>25. Lithuania maintaining non committal attitude Polish and Russian
                                efforts to enlist her support and has requested advice of England
                                which has not yet replied but answer expected shortly. Chief of
                                French military mission Kovno leaving to-day for Warsaw to ascertain
                                maximum Polish concession to Lithuania in return for latter’s
                                friendly neutrality.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>